Create an Activation for an External Platform

Create an activation to publish a segment to an external activation target.

On the Activations tab, click New.
Select a data space.
Select a segment to activate.

The segment must have an active publish schedule to ensure that near real-time membership data is sent.

Select an activation target.

If the privacy type isn’t set, update the external platform to include a privacy type.

Select the Individual data model object (DMO) from Activation Membership.
Click Continue.
If you’re using a Google, LinkedIn, Meta, or Amazon Ads activation target, map each data model attribute to its partner field.
Select the object and field where the data is stored.
Select the path to retrieve the data from the object.
Click Save.
Click Next.
For each contact point mapped:
Select the maximum number of attribute values to be sent per Individual.
Select a sort option for the attribute values.
Click Next.
Provide a name and optional description for the activation and save. Use this name to find the activated audience within your external platform.
